This paper discusses the role of part-of-speech (POS) tags in neural dependency parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the arXiv category of Computer Science - Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also uses multi-task learning frameworks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of character-based word representations, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks for natural language processing (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
